- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with depth estimation from monocular videos, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as depth estimation is an important task in robotics for navigation and obstacle avoidance. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper proposes a novel unsupervised learning framework for depth estimation. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with a problem that is relevant to AI applications such as autonomous driving. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with generating high resolution depth maps, which is relevant to graphics applications such as virtual reality and augmented reality.
